{"word":"G5217 - ὑπάγω - hypágō - hoop-ag'-o - Depart","slug":"G5217","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">ὑπάγω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>hypágō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>hoop-ag'-o"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Depart"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C5;&#x0314;&#x03C0;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03B3;&#x03C9; - hupago&#x0304;</b> - <i>hoop-ag'-o</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/G5259\">G5259</a> and <a href=\"#/G71\">G71</a>; to <i>lead</i> (oneself) <i>under</i>, that is, <i>withdraw</i> or <i>retire</i> (as if <i>sinking</i> out of sight), literally or figuratively: - depart, get hence, go (a-) way."}]}